        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 12 at 5:14PM MDT by NWS Grand Junction CO</headline>
        <description>At 514 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 21
miles north of New Castle, or 23 miles north of Glenwood Springs,
moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Buford.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
